notes: No play possible on the originally scheduled date of September 5 due to rain and a wet ground.
Match delayed for 85 minutes due to wet field. Match reduced to 45 overs per side.
Healy's run out was at first given not out by the square leg umpire. The Indian fielders, however, protested and eventually the third umpire was called to decide.
Bevan hit a 4 to win the match
Australia to meet Sri Lanka in the final

milestones.description: Ganguly and Sunil Joshi's 100-run partnership is IND's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 92 between Syed Kirmani and Sandeep Patil
